Our goal is to live a life that is pleasing to Him and that is a witness of His love and life to our world. (John 15:1-10) LOVE OTHERS – Next to our relationship with God, our second priority is to love people. One of the ways Jesus said the world would know they are His disciples is that they would have love for one another. At Geyer Springs they seek to love each other as part of God’s family and to extend that love to a lost and hurting world. God has called us to demonstrate His love to people inside our church fellowship as well as to those outside they are called to reach. (John 13:35, I John 4:7, Matthew 25:40) REACH THE NATIONS – Our vision is not just for us and our city — it is global. God has called us to carry the Gospel to all the world. All the world is both across the street and around the world. As they obey this calling from God, they seek to help every member find his or her place as they all work together to REACH THE NATIONS. Description: Consignd operates a virtual consignment marketplace that enables users to sell products through an expert.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Consignd’s story begins and ends with the maker. Our goal is to change the rules of online retail to benefit those behind the creation of products and those who share their stories. Traditionally, online retailers have justified taking up to 60% of the retail price of products because they alone have had the capacity to get inventory in front of large audiences. In the past few years, with the growth of sites like Pinterest, Svpply, and Tumblr, that job is increasingly being done by writers, bloggers, and regular people like you or I. Consignd takes the old retail model and removes the retailer, instead relying on this new form of social distribution. The outcome is simple: consumers can buy directly from the maker, makers get their stories heard across the web, and those who helped share them share in their success. Consignd is made with love in NYC.
